metadata.name: suniswap
metadata.description: SuniSwap - Concentrated Liquidity AMM with V4-style Hooks on Solana

fields.name: config
docs: The config this fee tier belongs to

fields.name: fee_rate
docs: Fee rate in hundredths of a basis point (100 = 0.01%)

fields.name: tick_spacing
docs: Tick spacing for this fee tier
Lower fee = tighter spacing for stable pairs

types.name: Pool
docs: Pool state - the core AMM state for a token pair
Using zero-copy for efficient memory access and reduced stack usage
All fields are carefully ordered to avoid implicit padding

fields.name: sqrt_price_x64
docs: Current sqrt price as Q64.64 fixed point

fields.name: fee_growth_global_a_x128
docs: Global fee growth for token A (Q64.128)

fields.name: fee_growth_global_b_x128
docs: Global fee growth for token B (Q64.128)

fields.name: protocol_fees_a
docs: Protocol fees accumulated for token A

fields.name: protocol_fees_b
docs: Protocol fees accumulated for token B

fields.name: protocol_fee_rate
docs: Protocol fee rate (percentage of swap fees)

fields.name: hook_flags
docs: Hook flags indicating which hooks are enabled

fields.name: config
docs: The config this pool belongs to

fields.name: token_mint_a
docs: Token A mint (must be < token B mint lexicographically)

fields.name: token_vault_a
docs: Token A vault (PDA owned by pool)

fields.name: token_vault_b
docs: Token B vault (PDA owned by pool)

fields.name: hook_program
docs: Hook program address (zero if no hooks)

types.name: Position
docs: Liquidity position - represents an LP's concentrated liquidity in a pool
Using zero-copy for efficient memory access
Fields ordered by alignment requirements to avoid padding

fields.name: liquidity
docs: Amount of liquidity in this position

fields.name: fee_growth_inside_a_last_x128
docs: Fee growth inside the position's range at last update (token A)

fields.name: fee_growth_inside_b_last_x128
docs: Fee growth inside the position's range at last update (token B)

fields.name: tokens_owed_a
docs: Uncollected fees owed to the position (token A)

fields.name: tokens_owed_b
docs: Uncollected fees owed to the position (token B)

fields.name: tick_lower
docs: Lower tick of the position range

fields.name: tick_upper
docs: Upper tick of the position range

fields.name: pool
docs: The pool this position belongs to

fields.name: position_mint
docs: Position NFT mint (optional, for NFT-based positions)

fields.name: protocol_authority
docs: Authority that can update protocol settings

fields.name: default_protocol_fee_rate
docs: Default protocol fee rate (percentage of swap fees taken by protocol)

fields.name: pool_creation_paused
docs: Whether new pool creation is paused

types.name: Tick
docs: Tick data - stored within tick arrays
Each tick represents a price point where liquidity can change
Using zero-copy compatible layout with proper alignment

fields.name: liquidity_net
docs: Net liquidity change when crossing this tick (positive = liquidity added)
When price moves up through tick: add liquidity_net
When price moves down through tick: subtract liquidity_net

fields.name: liquidity_gross
docs: Used to track when tick can be uninitialized

fields.name: fee_growth_outside_a_x128
docs: Fee growth on the other side of this tick (token A)
Stored relative to current tick for efficient range calculations

fields.name: fee_growth_outside_b_x128
docs: Fee growth on the other side of this tick (token B)

fields.name: seconds_outside
docs: Seconds spent on the other side of this tick

types.name: TickArray
docs: Tick Array - stores a contiguous range of tick data
Using zero-copy for efficient memory access
Fields ordered to ensure proper alignment (Tick needs 16-byte alignment)

fields.name: pool
docs: The pool this tick array belongs to

fields.name: start_tick_index
docs: Starting tick index for this array

fields.name: initialized_bitmap
docs: Bitmap of initialized ticks (1 byte = 8 bits)

fields.name: _padding
docs: Padding to align ticks array to 16 bytes (40 -> 48)

fields.name: ticks
docs: Array of ticks (8 ticks per array, each 96 bytes)
